Internal CSS
-------------

<head>
    <style>
    ---- Selectors----
Selector is the process(concept), which simply tells which property corresponding to its value is going to be implemented on which element.

Types of selectors : 
        1. Element selector (Tag selector)
        2. Id selector(#)
        3. Class selector(.)
        4. Universal selector(*)
        5. Grouping selector(seperated by comma)
        6. Descendant selector
        7. Advance Selector
            a. Adjacent sibling selector(+)
            b. Direct child selector(>)
            c. General sibling selector(~)
            d. Attribute selector
            e. :nth-of-type()
        8. Pseudo class selector(:)
        9. Pseudo element selector(::)
    </style>
</head>
